  <Summary>The Empire of Turan's soldiers join Conan in his unholy fight!

*Contents*
"The Stalker Amid the Sands" - continues Roy Thomas, John Buscema and Ricardo Villamonte's adaptation of Andrew J. Offutt's novel "Conan and the Sorcerer"
~"Half-human, half-monster, it prowls the wastelands 'twixt Shadizar and Zamboula - and even Conan's savage sword cannot do it harm"~
"Satan's Swordbearers" - a study of the mercenary armies of the Hyborian Age by Fred Blosser
"The Chan Barbarians" - a two page pin-up by Ernie Chan
"Wings in the Night" - the second part of the Solomon Kane tale adapted by Don Glut and David Wenzel
a pin-up by Joe Jusko
a frontispiece pin-up by Carl Potts and Neal Adams</Summary>
